20/01/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Army Chief of Staff General Mihail Popescu said Monday (19 January) that the Armed Forces currently employ around 93,000 military and 24,000 civilian staff. 
In addition, the army relies on about 100,000 reservists. 
Planned reforms will downsize the armed forces to 75,000 military and 15,000 civilian staff by 2007 but will expand the reserve forces to 110,000.
In other news Monday, Romania and Turkey signed an agreement on readmission of citizens, aimed at easing the exchange illegal immigrants and suspected criminals. 
(Rompres, Nine o'Clock - 20/01/04; Mediafax, Anadolu Agency - 19/01/04)
